<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900801-0072</DOCNO><DOCID>900801-0072.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- MCI Communications Corp.:   Purchase of Telecom USA   Is Approved by the FCC</HL><DATE>08/01/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A16</SO><CO>   MCIC TTT</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)TELEPHONE SYSTEMS (TLS)</IN><GV>FEDERAL COMMUNICATIONS COMMISSION (FCC)</GV><LP>   The Federal Communications Commission approved MCICommunications Corp.'s planned acquisition of Telecom USAInc., Atlanta.   The agency's Common Carrier Bureau found that thecombination &quot;would continue to be subject to vigorouscompetition&quot; from American Telephone andamp; Telegraph Co., UnitedTelecommunications' Sprint Communications Corp. unit andother long-distance carriers. MCI is the U.S.'s secondlargest long-distance company, and Telecom USA is the fourthlargest.</LP><TEXT>   An MCI spokeswoman said the company expects to completethe $1.25 billion merger this month after receiving approvalfrom various state regulators.</TEXT></DOC>